300	// Returns [verb, arg1, arg2, ...] where the final argument absorbs any
301	// remaining whitespace-separated words as a single string. Surrounding
302	// double-quotes on the final argument are stripped.
303	//
304	// For directives that need 3 distinct args (modify-line: path regex repl)
305	// we return verb + 3 separate fields: parts[0..2], with parts[3:] joined
306	// onto the last field.
